“租售同权”被疫情打出原形。
"Same rights to hire and sell" by the outbreak of the original form.
饶贤君2020-02-11 16:35。
Rap Yin Jun 2020-02-11 16: 35.
扫描二维码分享到朋友圈。
Scanning two-dimensional code to share with friends.
经济观察网 记者 饶贤君伴随着新冠肺炎疫情的发展，一张题为《这次疫情给了我们八个提示》的图片在各大社交平台流传，第一个建议就是——能买房的时候，别犹豫，不要被那些名人不买房的理由欺骗了，特殊时期，房东不租给你，酒店进不去。
Rao Xianjun, a reporter with the Economic Watch, accompanied the development of the new crown pneumonia epidemic. A picture of the epidemic giving us eight tips was circulated on social networking platforms. The first suggestion was to buy a house without hesitation and not to be fooled by the reasons that celebrities do not buy it.
。
.
疫情面前，“租客”成了一个尴尬的身份，北京、杭州、西安、宁波、南京、苏州等多个城市，相继出现了以防范疫情为由，对无论是否来自疫区、身体是否健康的租客一律禁入、劝返的事件。
In the face of the epidemic, "tenants" have become an embarrassing status, Beijing, Hangzhou, Xi'an, Ningbo, Nanjing, Suzhou and other cities, have emerged to prevent the outbreak of epidemic, whether or not from the epidemic area, whether the health of tenants, or not, the event.
。
.
疑问随之而来，当租客依法享有的基本租住权、房屋使用权都被限制，“租售同权”又该从何谈起？。
The question then arises, when the tenant enjoys the basic tenancy right, the right to use the house is restricted, "lease sale the same right" how to start?
“谁的权力剥夺了我的权利？”。
"Whose power has deprived me of my rights?"
“我的手机充电宝都没电了，我现在要想办法去超市充一点电，再要一些热水煮一碗泡面。
"I'm running out of battery chargers on my cell phone. I'm going to go to the supermarket and get some hot water to boil a bowl of noodles.
”齐金华已经连着吃了四顿泡面，2月9日夜里，他在杭州市滨江区的一个24小时ATM玻璃房里蹲坐着睡着，2月10日的夜晚温度是9摄氏度，他打算买一床被子和一个靠枕。
Qi Jinhua, who had eaten four consecutive meals of noodles, spent the night of February 9 squatting in a 24-hour ATM glass room in Hangzhou's Binjiang district, February 10, when the temperature was 9 degrees Celsius.
。
.
按照滨江区此前发布的《冠状病毒肺炎防控指挥部令第四号》，各租户不得在2月9日24时前返杭，而齐金华所在工厂要求2月10日复工，因此，齐金华在2月9日22时到达了杭州，并在24时后尝试进入小区。
According to the previous Order of the Binjiang District No. 4 on the Prevention and Control of Coronavirus Pneumonia, all tenants are not allowed to return to Hangzhou before 2400 hours on February 9. Qi Jinhua therefore returned to Hangzhou at 2200 hours on February 9 and tried to enter the area after 2400 hours.
。
.
物业给出的答案是不行。
The answer given by the property is no.
。
.
齐金华试图用政府文件说服物业，没有任何效果，“值班的物业说，他们没有收到指令说可以进去，那就不可以进去，我想进去就去找居委会”。
Qi Jinhua tried to persuade the property with government documents, but to no avail. "The property on duty said they had not received instructions to go in, so they could not go in.
。
.
既然政府文件并非直接参考意见，租户禁入的指令从何而来？。
Since the Government document is not a direct reference, where does the Tenant Prohibition Order come from?
2月10日一早，被冻醒的齐金华收到了工厂暂未复工的消息，他第一时间赶去了社区居委会，居委会工作人员的回复是，没有收到允许租户进入社区的任何通知，所以不能进去，谁让你过来的，你让谁解决，有居住问题，去找工厂解决。
On the morning of February 10, Qi Jinhua, who had been awakened by the freeze, received news that the factory had not resumed work. He immediately went to the neighbourhood committee, which responded that no notice had been received allowing tenants to enter the community, so they could not go in.
。
.
齐金华又找到了工厂负责人，对方表示，齐金华的小区在“瞎搞”，让他联系市长热线举报投诉。
Qi Jinhua again found the factory director, the other side said that Qi Jinhua's small area "nonsense", let him contact the mayor hotline to report complaints.
。
.
而市长热线的答复是，一切以社区、物业具体措施为准。
The Mayor's hotline responded that all community, property-specific measures to prevail.
。
.
齐金华的回家之路陷入了死局，物业称指令来自居委会，居委会的通知发自政府部门，而政府部门又将“具体措施”下放给了物业和居委会。
Qi Jinhua's way home fell into a dead end, property said the directive came from the neighborhood committee, the notice from the government department, which in turn delegated the "concrete measures" to the property and neighborhood committee.
。
.
政策出现了末端失效。
There was an end-of-pipe failure.
。
.
2月10日午间，杭州市《“冠状病毒肺炎”防控指挥部令第34号》发布，指出不得随意限制小区居民和租客进入小区。
February 10 noon, Hangzhou "coronavirus pneumonia" control and control command order No. 34 issued, said that no arbitrary restrictions on residents and tenants of small residential areas into the community.
然而，当齐金华等众多租户拿着红头文件再次试图进入小区，得到的答案依然是禁入。
However, when many tenants, such as Qi Jinhua, tried to enter the community again with red-headed documents, the answer was still no access.
。
.
齐金华在几个社交平台发问：不让我回小区这事合法吗？是谁的权力剥夺了我的权利？。
Qi Jinhua asked on several social platforms: Is it legal not to let me go back to the community? Whose power deprives me of my rights?
同样的困惑正困扰着数以万计的租户，2.1万人在微博“杭州封小区”等相关话题下讨论着租户有家不能回的困扰，一位回到杭州的抖音主播拍下了从老家出发回到杭州，被劝返后睡公园、睡烂尾楼的短视频，收获了数十万的点赞和评论。
The same confusion is plaguing tens of thousands of tenants, with 21,000 people discussing issues such as "Hangzhou Sealing Community" and other related topics. One returning to Hangzhou filmed a short video of returning from his hometown to Hangzhou, where he was persuaded to sleep in a park and in a dilapidated building, where hundreds of thousands of comments were made.
。
.
除了杭州，在北京、西安、宁波、南京、苏州等许多城市，“租户不得进入”被写在了大大小小的通知告示之上。
In addition to Hangzhou, in many cities such as Beijing, Xi'an, Ningbo, Nanjing and Suzhou, "no-go" notices have been written on large and small notice boards.
。
.
武汉大学健康学院教授谭晓东表示，站在保护易感人群的角度，社区的做法可以理解，但是，从社会发展的角度分析，只有生产发展才是硬道理，租户回社区也是为了生产，所以，只要能证明其是健康的，而且做好防护措施，租户回社区是可行的，“原理好说，事情难做，过程需要细致的工作”。
Tan Xiaodong, a professor at Wuhan University School of Health, said the community approach was understandable in terms of protecting vulnerable groups, but that from a social development perspective, only productive development and tenant return to the community was feasible, so long as it could be proved that it was healthy and protected, "said Tan Xiaodong, professor of health at Wuhan University.
。
.
租售何时同权。
When to lease and sell.
2017年7月，住建部首次明确将通过立法，明确租赁当事人的权利义务，保障当事人的合法权益，建立稳定租期和租金等方面的制度，逐步使租房居民在基本公共服务方面与买房居民享有同等待遇。
In July 2017, the Ministry of Housing and Construction will, for the first time, adopt legislation to clarify the rights and obligations of the parties concerned, guarantee their legitimate rights and interests, establish a stable tenancy period and rent system, and gradually give them the same treatment as buyers in respect of basic public services.
。
.
而此次对租户劝返、禁入力度最大的杭州，正是2017年住建部公布的12大租售同权试点城市之一。
Hangzhou, home to the largest number of tenants, is one of the 12 major rental and sales pilot cities announced by the Ministry of Housing in 2017.
。
.
在成为租售同权试点城市之后，杭州市很快于2017年8月推出了《杭州市加快培育和发展住房租赁市场试点工作方案》（以下简称《方案》），提出19条具体措施，鼓励住房租赁市场发展，完善、保障租房者权利。
After becoming a pilot city for leasing and selling the same rights, Hangzhou launched the Experimental Work Program of Hangzhou City for Accelerating Housing Leasing Market (hereinafter referred to as "the Program") in August 2017, proposing 19 concrete measures to encourage the development of the housing rental market and improve and safeguard the rights of tenants.
。
.
教育问题是租售同权问题的核心，杭州在《方案》中提出，承租人依法办理《浙江省居住证》后，其子女入学按照《流动人口随迁子女在杭州市区接受学区教育和义务教育管理办法(试行)》有关规定执行，即租赁房屋，子女也可就近上学，在杭州市居住证积分管理中，对租赁住房达到一定年限的，实行“租购同分”。
Education is the core of the issue of the same right to rent and sell. In the Plan, Hangzhou proposes that after the lessee carries out the Residence Permit in Zhejiang Province according to law, the children can also go to school nearby according to the Regulations on the Administration of School District Education and Compulsory Education in Hangzhou.
。
.
但多位知情人士表示，就近上学实际在操作中并没有想象中简单，租户想要让孩子上教育资源较好的知名公立学校，可能性几乎为零。
But a number of people familiar with the matter said that proximity to school was not as simple as might be expected, and that tenants were almost impossible to get their children to attend well-known public schools with better educational resources.
。
.
杭州市政府在官网上发布的《方案》解读称，未来杭州市在建设国家租赁市场试点城市的工作中，指导思想是：以满足新市民住房需求为主要出发点，以建立购租并举的住房制度为主要方向，以市场为主满足多层次需求，以政府为主满足基本保障，建立健全住房租赁体系，支持住房租赁消费，引导居民转变住房消费观念，促进住房租赁市场健康发展。
In the future, Hangzhou will focus on meeting the housing needs of the new residents, taking the housing system as the main orientation, satisfying multi-level needs with the market as the main orientation, establishing and improving the housing leasing system, supporting housing rental consumption, guiding residents to change their concept of housing consumption and promoting healthy development of the housing rental market.
。
.
然而，在疫情的“试金石”下，租售权利之间的不平等凸显。
However, in the "touchstone" of the epidemic, the inequality between the right to rent and sell stands out.
。
.
据了解，各地对租户及业主之间存在明显的差别待遇，例如，杭州余杭区的多个村社发布通知，来自湖北或是浙江温州等疫情严重地区，业主经过医学检查合格，就可以进入小区回到家中自我隔离，而普通租户如果来自疫情严重地区，则无论身体情况如何一律劝返。
It is understood that there are obvious differences between tenants and owners. For example, several rural communities in Hangzhou Yuhang District have issued notices that owners from areas with serious epidemics, such as Hubei or Wenzhou in Zhejiang Province, can enter the small areas and return to their homes to isolate themselves.
。
.
这并非个例，各个社交平台上，网友们晒出了浙江、江苏、河南、广东等多地的类似文件，在同样条件下，业主能回而租客不能回的事比比皆是。
This is not the case, various social platforms, netizens basked in Zhejiang, Jiangsu, Henan, Guangdong and other similar documents, under the same conditions, owners can return and tenants can not return the matter.
。
.
多位律师向记者表示，现阶段，并没有法律支持各地社区、街道、物业甚至政府剥夺租户应有的基本权利，更何况是在大部分租户身体健康的情况下，于情于理于法都不该“一刀切”，租户的租住权利与业主的权利一样受到法律保护。
A number of lawyers told reporters that at this stage, there is no law to support communities, streets, properties and even the government to deprive tenants of their basic rights. Moreover, given that most tenants are in good health, there should be no "one size fits all" in the law. Tenants' tenancy rights enjoy the same legal protection as those of owners.
。
.
一位律师对记者表示，租售同权，“同”的不仅是享受公共服务的权利，更应该是任何时期、任何理由都不能肆意侵犯的法定基本权利，“如果连最基本的权利都无法从根本的理念上达成认同，租售同权就只是表面文章”。
A lawyer told reporters that the right to rent and sell is not only a right to public services, but also a fundamental legal right that cannot be violated at any time or for any reason.
。
.
